CAPE TOWN: South Africa&#39;s cabinet said on Thursday the police were investigating allegations that State Security Minister David Mahlobo was involved in a rhino-poaching syndicate. Mahlobo has denied any wrongdoing. The allegations against the minister emerged in an Al Jazeera documentary this week. &quot;Cabinet noted the allegations in an Al Jazeera documentary against the Minister of State Security, David Mahlobo, and noted that the South African police services are investigating these allegations,&quot; the cabinet said in a statement.